title: Great Britain : Divorce rate 2000 to 2017
summary: In general Divorce rate per thousad married person has fallen over the Year.

Divorce rate per thousad married person is roughly constant from 2002 to 2004, gradually decreasing from 2004 to 2009, roughly constant from 2009 to 2013, and lastly slightly decreasing from 2013 to 2017.
The highest Divorce rate per thousad married person, of value 13.3 was reached at Year 2003, and 2004
Minimum Divorce rate per thousad married person about 8.4 was reached at Year 2017
